    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "Is this skill compatible with older Next.js versions?",
        "answer": "This skill targets Next.js 15 specifically. Some patterns like Server Components and App Router work in Next.js 13+, but syntax may differ."
      },
      {
        "question": "What are the limits of the Server Component patterns?",
        "answer": "Server Components cannot use hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers. Move interactivity to Client Components and wrap with Suspense."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I use this with other UI component libraries?",
        "answer": "This skill focuses on Shadcn/ui patterns. The general principles apply to other libraries but import paths and class names will differ."
      },
      {
        "question": "Is my data safe when using Server Components?",
        "answer": "Yes. Server Components execute on your infrastructure. Data never leaves your server - it is fetched and rendered before sending HTML to the client."
      },
      {
        "question": "Why is my component rendering on the client instead of server?",
        "answer": "Check for 'use client' directive at the top. If missing, ensure no hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers are used. Remove any client-side patterns."
      },
